summary:
The Security Council, recalling its previous resolutions on the arms embargo on Libya, including resolution 1970 (2011) and subsequent relevant resolutions, and resolutions 2292 (2016), 2357 (2017), 2420 (2018), 2473 (2019), 2526 (2020), and 2578 (2021) on the implementation of the arms embargo on the high seas off Libya's coast, reaffirms its resolution 2570 (2021) and recognizes the role of neighboring countries and regional organizations. Acting under Chapter VII of the UN Charter, the Council: 
1. Extends the authorizations in resolution 2578 (2021) for 12 months; 
2. Requests the Secretary-General to report on implementation at six and eleven months; 
3. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
